{
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, this subspace is mapped into H L (P Y, p 1, p 1) = {0} which is trivial by Theorem 4.6 and the fact that Z(C)(Y * → 1) = {0}.",
    "By noting that the operator Dr(1 1→X X) L (Dr (1 1→X X) L) * = d -1 X Dr L    acts as identity on the remaining subspace H L (P 1, p X, p X) (again see [32,Remark 3.14]), we obtain the second claim.",
    "The hopping operator Dr( X 1→1 X) Lannihilates the orthogonal complement of H L (id, p X, p 1) = H L (P X, p X, p 1) by definition, and the operator (Dr( X 1→1 X) L) * Dr ( X 1→1 X) L = Dr L id X⊗1acts on this subspace as the identity.",
    "This shows the third equality.",
    "The proof of the last equality is identical to that of the third."
  ]
